{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-03905/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-03905"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:39:05"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["dirty single"]}}],"summary":{"none":["One woman speaks to another."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03905/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-03905","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03905/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-03905"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03905/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03905/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03905/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03905/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03905/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03905/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03905/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03905/canvas/1/0e751c54-2e88-49a3-ad55-4ac7e50f8760","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T17:51:09.477Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The interplay of light and shadow in this scene underscores the back-and-forth and contrasting personalities of Alma and Cyril. The former is frequently seen in bright, bold colors, while the latter prefers dark ones.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03905/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:412.16689098250333,788.7213997308211,422.50336473755056,206.72947510094195"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03905/canvas/1/d0094cb0-fcca-4f54-bee2-d9795e5bd290","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T17:51:25.544Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Alma accuses Reynolds of “being too fussy,” adopting language befitting a mother taking care of a child. Reynold’s personality, it seems, was partially based on that of Cristóbal Balenciaga. As his biography Mary Blume writes, “To atough cookie like [Coco] Chanel, Balenciaga’s vulnerability seemed a weakness; his staff knew it was his strength. He was friable by nature and so they made his house into a cocoon where he could work undisturbed and they welcomed to the salon only those who were welcome” (Blume, <em>The Master of Us All</em>, 93).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03905/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:664.1184387617766,314.53566621803503,507.77927321668903,423.7954239569314"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03905/canvas/1/70ebf020-7c6f-4390-95e6-c3f02aed62bf","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T17:51:41.544Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>This sequence of <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW7712267 BCX4\" href=\"https://ptannotated.com/items/phan-03942.html\"><u>shot-reverse shot</u></a> utilizes low-key lighting to present Alma and Cyril’s visages as bifurcated by shadow. The resulting cuts frame these two women as inverses or mirrors—Alma’s right side bathed in light, Cyril’s left—their interplay both triangulated by and independent of Reynolds.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03905/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:103.36473755047109,85.84118438761789,399.24629878869445,244.1991924629878"}}}]}]}]}